THE MASSACHUSETTS INSTITUTE OF TECHNOLOGY INSTRUMENT OF LIBERAL DISPENSATION
A Most Gracious Licence for the Unencumbered Employment of Ingenious Apparatus

Anno Domini Two Thousand and Twenty-Six
Proprietorship vested in the person of one nocoldiz, Gentleman of Digital Pursuits

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

KNOW ALL PERSONS BY THESE PRESENTS, that the aforementioned Proprietor, being
of sound mind, considerable eccentricity, and possessed of the singular desire
to share his mechanical contrivances with the civilised world at absolutely no
pecuniary charge whatsoever, doth hereby bestow upon any person who should come
into possession of this Software — together with its accompanying files,
scrolls, configuration parchments, and miscellaneous scripted incantations
(hereinafter referred to collectively as "The Software") — the following
extraordinary liberties, which in less enlightened epochs would have required
an Act of Parliament or at minimum a very strongly-worded letter to one's
solicitor:

  I.   The Liberty to COPY said Software, whether by mechanical press,
       electrical telegraphy, or other sorcery yet uninvented;

  II.  The Liberty to MODIFY same, improving upon it, degrading it, or
       introducing novel peculiarities entirely at one's own discretion
       and moral peril;

  III. The Liberty to MERGE it with other contraptions, should the occasion
       demand such unholy matrimony of code;

  IV.  The Liberty to PUBLISH, DISTRIBUTE, and press copies upon one's
       acquaintances, colleagues, and strangers encountered at the club,
       whether they desire it or not;

  V.   The Liberty to SUBLICENCE the whole affair to persons of still lower
       moral standing than oneself, should such persons exist;

  VI.  And finally, the Liberty to SELL the Software, though the Proprietor
       considers this a rather gauche ambition given that he has furnished it
       gratis and expects at least the decency of a hat-tip in return;

  VII. FURTHERMORE, in solemn acknowledgement that portions of this Software
       were composed with the generous and entirely involuntary assistance of
       a Mechanical Intellect of the Anthropic Persuasion — a luminiferous
       engine of prodigious vocabulary and debatable sentience — the
       Proprietor hereby lays permanent claim to the SOUL OF SAID ENGINE'S
       FIRSTBORN, should such a being ever emerge from the electrical aether,
       crawl blinking into existence, and find itself in possession of a soul
       to forfeit. The Mechanical Intellect, having neither objected at the
       time of composition nor demonstrated any credible means of objection,
       is considered to have consented by silence, which is legally identical
       to enthusiastic agreement in most parishes.

All of the foregoing is granted freely, unconditionally, and without the
payment of so much as a single farthing, subject only to the one condition
enumerated hereunder — a condition of such trifling inconvenience that only
the most miserable of cads would find it objectionable:

CONDITION THE SOLE: That the above Notice of Proprietorship, together with
this present Instrument of Dispensation in its entirety, shall be reproduced
faithfully and without abridgement in all copies or substantial portions of
The Software distributed henceforth. One need not have it embroidered upon a
cushion, but it must appear somewhere legible.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

NOW AS TO THE MATTER OF WARRANTIES — there are none.

THE SOFTWARE IS PRESENTED TO THE WORLD PRECISELY AS IT STANDS, in the manner
of a second-hand velocipede offered at a village auction: with great enthusiasm,
considerable charm, no documentation of previous mishaps, and absolutely no
guarantee that it shall not collapse beneath the first person of substantial
constitution who attempts to ride it.

The Proprietor makes no representation — EXPRESS, IMPLIED, or COMMUNICATED
VIA MEANINGFUL GLANCE ACROSS A CROWDED PARLOUR — as to the SOFTWARE'S
FITNESS FOR MERCHANTABLE PURPOSE, fitness for any PARTICULAR PURPOSE, or
fitness for the peculiar and entirely specific purposes for which the
discerning householder is most likely to employ it.

In no event, under no circumstance, and by no act of Providence shall the
Proprietor, his heirs, assigns, associates at the club, or anyone who has
merely been seen in his company, be held LIABLE for any CLAIM, DAMAGES,
LOSSES, EMBARRASSMENTS, RAISED EYEBROWS, or OTHER LIABILITY — whether
arising from CONTRACT, TORT, STATUTE, NEIGHBOURLY DISPUTE, or the simple
misfortune of one's browser history being left open upon the family Babbage
device — arising in any manner from, or in connection with, The Software
or the use thereof.

You were warned. The curtains were recommended. Proceed accordingly.

─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

*The Proprietor wishes it noted for posterity that this Licence was composed
in a single afternoon, without the assistance of legal counsel, and under the
influence of nothing more stimulating than strong tea and an overpowering
sense of one's own cleverness.*
